<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}-{9}{y}=-{42}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}{x}-{7}{y}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({3},{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+-{9}{y}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{42}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{42}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{\left(\frac{{-{42}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}\right)}+-{7}{y}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{2}}{{-{{5}}}}\cdot{\left(-{42}\right)}-\frac{{2}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left(-{9}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{16.8}-{\left(-{3.6}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3.6}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}=-{15}-{16.8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3.6}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}=-{31.8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3.6}+{\left(-{7}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{31.8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10.6}{y}=-{31.8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{31.8}}{{-{{10.6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+-{9}{\left({3}\right)}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left(-{27}\right)}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{42}-{\left(-{27}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{15}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({3},{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

